osing a method that takes advantage of digital resources like full-text databases but still depends on the interpreter to fashion ideas out of ordinary language. Five Words is an innovative and accessible book that points the field of literary studies in an exciting new direction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aComparative literature. 0aSemantics, ComparativexHistory. 70(DE-601)1045587250(DE-588)4138097-6aWortfeld2gnd 70(DE-601)1046750390(DE-588)4079262-6aWiderstand2gnd 70(DE-601)1046976280(DE-588)4255333-7aKontrastive Semantik2gnd 70(DE-601)10611946X0(DE-588)4065341-9aWelt2gnd 70(DE-601)1061547450(DE-588)4056449-6aSprache2gnd 70(DE-601)1062450150(DE-588)4035964-5aLiteratur2gnd 70(DE-601)1063375640(DE-588)4015223-6aErfindung2gnd 70(DE-601)1063742140(DE-588)4007259-9aBlut2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  ashakespeare, critical, critics, critique, academic, scholarly, college, university, cervantes, famous authors, classics, literature, literary canon, british, england, europe, european, research, language, invention, blood, resistance, world, semantics, 16th century, 1500s, science, politics, interdisciplinary, analysis, renaissance, transatlantic, camoes, milton, digital, database, comparative.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022600063340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226000770423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226000770/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles